      "text": [
        " مَلَكَانِ يُفَرِّجَانِ لِلنَّاسِ لَيْلَةَ مُزْدَلِفَةَ عِنْدَ الْمَأْزِمَيْنِ الضَّيِّقَيْنِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "And from him, from Ali Bin Al Numan, from Saeed Al A’araj, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Two Angels make way for the people on the night of Muzdalifa at the two narrow points’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. It is narrated from him (narrator of previous Hadith) from Ali ibn al-Nu’man from Sa‘id al-’A‘raj who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Two angels make room for people who become congested in al-Mazemin.’” "
        ]
      }
